  "steps": [
    {
      "title": "Simplify the absolute values using the constraint a < 0",
      "content": "Since $a \\lt 0$, both $16a$ and $9a$ are negative. Taking absolute values:<ul><li>$|16a| = -(16a) = -16a$</li><li>$|9a| = -(9a) = -9a$</li></ul>"
    },
    {
      "title": "Evaluate $f(16a)$ and $f(9a)$",
      "content": "$$f(16a) = \\frac{-16a}{a} - 15 = -16 - 15 = -31$$<br/>$$f(9a) = \\frac{-9a}{a} - 15 = -9 - 15 = -24$$"
    },
    {
      "title": "Multiply to find the answer",
      "content": "$$f(16a) \\times f(9a) = (-31) \\times (-24) = 744$$<br/>The answer is <strong>744</strong>."
    }
  ]
}